{"title":"Aura of Abjuration","url":"http://crawl.chaosforge.org/Aura_of_Abjuration","type":"markdown","data":"***Obsolete**: This article refers to an aspect of the game which has been removed. It is retained for historical reference only.*\n\n| [![Aura of abjuration.png](/images/c/c6/Aura_of_abjuration.png)](/File:Aura_of_abjuration.png) Aura of Abjuration |                                                                |\n| :---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| Level                                                                                                             | 5                                                              |\n| School1                                                                                                           | [Summoning](/Summonings \"Summonings\")                          |\n| Source(s)                                                                                                         | [Book of Summonings](/Book_of_Summonings \"Book of Summonings\") |\n| [Casting noise](/Spell_noise \"Spell noise\")                                                                       | 5                                                              |\n| [Spell noise](/Spell_noise \"Spell noise\")                                                                         | 0                                                              |\n\n|   |                                                                                                                                                               |\n| - | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n|   | Continuously abjures hostile summoned creatures in the vicinity of the caster. This reduces their remaining time before being sent back where they came from. |\n\n**Aura of Abjuration** is a level 5 [Summoning](/Summonings \"Summonings\") spell which gives you an abjuration [aura](/Aura \"Aura\"). Any hostile summoned creatures within its range will have their duration reduced each turn, and will be dismissed entirely when their duration hits 0.\n\n## Strategy\n\n- You can cast this spell before combat with a summoner. This is usually worthwhile against opponents that have other means of hurting you badly from behind their summons; think [greater mummies](/Royal_mummy \"Royal mummy\") and [liches](/Lich \"Lich\"). In the mid-game, the spell works well against [deep elf demonologists](/Deep_elf_demonologist \"Deep elf demonologist\"), [boggarts](/Boggart \"Boggart\"), and [vampire magi](/Vampire_mage \"Vampire mage\").\n- Note that the spell has no effect on [durable summons](/Durable_summon \"Durable summon\") or [eldritch tentacles](/Eldritch_tentacle \"Eldritch tentacle\"). Also, [The Shining One](/The_Shining_One \"The Shining One\") protects [Seraph](/Seraph \"Seraph\")'s [divine summons](/Summon_Holies \"Summon Holies\") against abjuration.\n\n## History\n\n- The spell was removed in [0.26](/0.26 \"0.26\").\n- Prior to [0.17](/0.17 \"0.17\"), Aura of Abjuration was a level 6 spell and appeared solely in [Grand Grimoire](/Grand_Grimoire \"Grand Grimoire\").\n- Aura of Abjuration was added in [0.14](/0.14 \"0.14\"), replacing [Mass Abjuration](/Mass_Abjuration \"Mass Abjuration\").\n","html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html class=\"client-nojs\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/>\n<title>Aura of Abjuration - CrawlWiki</title>\n<script>document.documentElement.className = document.documentElement.className.replace( /(^|\\s)client-nojs(\\s|$)/, \"$1client-js$2\" );</script>\n<script>(window.RLQ=window.RLQ||[]).push(function(){mw.config.set({\"wgCanonicalNamespace\":\"\",\"wgCanonicalSpecialPageName\":false,\"wgNamespaceNumber\":0,\"wgPageName\":\"Aura_of_Abjuratio