=\"31\"/></a>\t\t\t\t\t\t</li>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div style=\"clear:both\"></div>\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t<script>(window.RLQ=window.RLQ||[]).push(function(){mw.config.set({\"wgPageParseReport\":{\"smw\":{\"limitreport-intext-parsertime\":0.001},\"limitreport\":{\"cputime\":\"0.116\",\"walltime\":\"0.395\",\"ppvisitednodes\":{\"value\":131,\"limit\":1000000},\"ppgeneratednodes\":{\"value\":671,\"limit\":1000000},\"postexpandincludesize\":{\"value\":1422,\"limit\":2097152},\"templateargumentsize\":{\"value\":273,\"limit\":2097152},\"expansiondepth\":{\"value\":5,\"limit\":40},\"expensivefunctioncount\":{\"value\":0,\"limit\":100},\"timingprofile\":[\"100.00%  329.957      1 -total\",\" 94.46%  311.666      1 Template:Spell\",\" 73.40%  242.183      8 Template:If\",\" 12.14%   40.071      1 Template:Summonings\",\"  3.10%   10.239      1 Template:Obsolete\",\"  2.24%    7.385      1 Template:Flavour\"]},\"cachereport\":{\"timestamp\":\"20240916182709\",\"ttl\":86400,\"transientcontent\":false}}});});</script><script>(window.RLQ=window.RLQ||[]).push(function(){mw.config.set({\"wgBackendResponseTime\":94});});</script>\n\t</body>\n</html>\n","rawPage":"{{obsolete}}\n{{spell\n|name=Aura of Abjuration\n|level=5\n|school1={{Summonings}}\n|school2=\n|school3=\n|castingnoise=5\n|spellnoise=0\n|sources=[[Book of Summonings]]\n}}\n{{flavour|Continuously abjures hostile summoned creatures in the vicinity of the caster. This reduces their remaining time before being sent back where they came from.}}\n\n'''Aura of Abjuration''' is a level 5 [[Summonings|Summoning]] spell which gives you an abjuration [[aura]]. Any hostile summoned creatures within its range will have their duration reduced each turn, and will be dismissed entirely when their duration hits 0.\n\n==Strategy==\n*You can cast this spell before combat with a summoner. This is usually worthwhile against opponents that have other means of hurting you badly from behind their summons; think [[royal mummy|greater mummies]] and [[lich]]es. In the mid-game, the spell works well against [[deep elf demonologist]]s, [[boggart]]s, and [[vampire mage|vampire magi]].\n*Note that the spell has no effect on [[durable summon]]s or [[eldritch tentacle]]s. Also, [[The Shining One]] protects [[Seraph]]'s [[Summon Holies|divine summons]] against abjuration.\n\n==History==\n*The spell was removed in [[0.26]].\n*Prior to [[0.17]], Aura of Abjuration was a level 6 spell and appeared solely in [[Grand Grimoire]].\n*Aura of Abjuration was added in [[0.14]], replacing [[Mass Abjuration]]."}